President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate two individuals to key administration posts. The first nominee is Dr. Leon Aron, who is currently the Resident Scholar and Director of Russian Studies at the American Enterprise Institute. He has held this position since 1993 and was also a weekly contributor at the Voice of America's Russian language radio and television show from 1990 to 2004. Dr. Aron has previously worked as an Adjunct Professor at Georgetown University and a Senior Policy Analyst at the Heritage Foundation. He received a B.A. from Moscow State Pedagogical Institute and an M.A. and Ph.D. from Columbia University.

The second nominee is Jeffery S. Hall, who is currently the President of The Capstone Group, a firm he co-founded in 2009. Prior to this, he served as the State Executive Director in Kentucky for the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Farm Service Agency from 2001 to 2009. He has also held positions at the University of Kentucky College of Agriculture and as a Legislative Assistant in the Office of U.S. Senator Mitch McConnell. Mr. Hall has been involved in various non-profit organizations and received a B.S. from Purdue University.